<http://www.spektrix.com/improvcentrevancouver/event/44801AVQJMVSBSCDMRGLRKNLTGJPHPNQG>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "The Games Lab";
  schema:description """
	<h1>The Games Lab</h1><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Time: </span>3:30pm – 5:30pm<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Age: </span>19+<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Level Required: </span>some improv experience is required (email <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"mailto:education@theimprovcentre.ca\">education@theimprovcentre.ca</a> if you’re not sure).<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Workshop Capacity: </span>14 people<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Cost: </span>$30<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Explore a series of classic shortform games, giving you the space to play, play, and play some more! Get key tips and tricks on how to be even more successful in your scene work as you learn about the different types of games and the “motors” that make them so much fun to play!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>REFUND POLICY:<span><br/></span>No refunds. Day one and two of training must be taken consecutively in the booked weekend to ensure a trusting and collaborative experience for all students. Completion of course and eligibility for class advancement requires full attendance.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>LOCK OUT POLICY:<span><br/></span>Doors will lock 15 minutes after the class begins. Late comers will not be permitted.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>WAITLIST:<span><br/></span>If a class is sold out for a date you're hoping to attend, you can write in to <span class=\"BoldText\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"mailto:boxoffice@theimprovcentre.ca\">boxoffice@theimprovcentre.ca</a></span> to be added to a waitlist. While TIC can't guarantee you'll get a spot, we'll reach out if we can fit you in the class.
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-05-23T15:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/improvcentrevancouver/files/4a44ee72-24a3-4ca6-aaed-1241a9b28856.jpg>;
